<bibRefCitation author="Lagowska, B. &amp; Martin, J. H. &amp; Hodgson, C. J." box="[373,636,721,747]" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" pagination="295 - 310" refId="ref5598" refString="Lagowska, B., Martin, J. H. &amp; Hodgson, C. J. (2017) A new species of Marsipococcus Cockerell &amp; Bueker (Hemiptera: Coccomorpha: Coccidae) from Malaysia. Zootaxa, 4358 (2), 295 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4358.2.4" type="journal article" year="2017">
≈Åagowska 
<emphasis box="[496,553,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
provided the following generic diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Bueker, Hodgson" authorityYear="1994" box="[1146,1317,722,747]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Marsipococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="573" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1317,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="573">Marsipococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (i) dorsal derm with radial lines extending mesad from the margin; (ii) a group of ventral tubular ducts present on either side of the genital opening; (iii) each stigmatic cleft with 2 stigmatic spines, 1 on the anterior margin and the other on the posterior margin; (iv) preopercular pores present or absent; (v) each anal plate without a subdiscal seta; (vi) multilocular disc pores, when present, each with 5 or 6 loculi; (vii) anal cleft with sclerotization around its anterior margin; (viii) marginal setae strongly spinose and pointed, subequal to or longer than stigmatic setae; and (ix) tibia and tarsus fused, without segmentation.
</paragraph>
